Delia’s, Catalog Company and Retailer, Up for Sale, NYT Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-02-25T05:12:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/delia-s-catalog-company-and-retailer-up-for-sale-nyt-reports.html
Delia’s, the U.S. retail and catalog
company for teenage girls, is up for sale, the New York Times
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the matter.  The company, which has a market value of about $60 million,
has prospected interest among potential buyers including private
equity firms, the newspaper reported.  Delia’s is also looking at other options, including capital
raising, the Times said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
